</div><h2 id="github-pages" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#github-pages"><span>GitHub Pages</span></a></h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Set the correct <a href="https://v2.vuepress.vuejs.org/zh/reference/config.html#base" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">base</a> option.</p>
<p>If you are going to publish to <code v-pre>https://&lt;USERNAME&gt;.github.io/</code>, you can skip this step because the default <code v-pre>base</code> is <code v-pre>&quot;/&quot;</code>.</p>
<p>If you are going to publish to <code v-pre>https://&lt;USERNAME&gt;.github.io/&lt;REPO&gt;/</code>, which means your repository address is <code v-pre>https://github.com/&lt;USERNAME&gt;/&lt;REPO&gt;</code>, set <code v-pre>base</code> to <code v-pre>&quot;/&lt;REPO&gt;/&quot;</code>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Choose the CI tool you want to use. Here we take <a href="https://github.com/features/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Actions</a> as an example.</p>
<p>Create the <code v-pre>.github/workflows/docs.yml</code> file to configure the workflow.</p>
</li>
</ol>
