<h2 id="gitlab-pages" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#gitlab-pages"><span>GitLab Pages</span></a></h2>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Set the correct <a href="https://v2.vuepress.vuejs.org/zh/reference/config.html#base" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">base</a> option.</p>
<p>If you are going to publish to <code v-pre>https://&lt;USERNAME&gt;.gitlab.io/</code>, you can skip this step, so the default <code v-pre>base</code> is <code v-pre>&quot;/&quot;</code>.</p>
<p>If you are going to publish to <code v-pre>https://&lt;USERNAME&gt;.gitlab.io/&lt;REPO&gt;/</code>, which means your repository address is <code v-pre>https://gitlab.com/&lt;USERNAME&gt;/&lt;REPO&gt;</code>, set <code v-pre>base</code> to <code v-pre>&quot;/&lt;REPO&gt;/&quot;</code>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Create the <code v-pre>.gitlab-ci.yml</code> file to configure the <a href="https://about.gitlab.com/stages-devops-lifecycle/continuous-integration/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitLab CI</a> workflow.</p>
